# Title: Brief description of this commit (50 chars or less)
# Format: <type>(<optional scope>): <description>
# Example: feat(auth): add user login feature
#
# Type descriptions:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation update
#   style    - Code formatting changes (no functional impact)
#   refactor - Code refactoring
#   perf     - Performance optimization
#   test     - Test related
#   chore    - Build/tooling/other
#


# Body: Detailed description of changes (optional)
# - Why was this change made?
# - What was changed?
# - How was it tested?
#


# Related Issue (optional)
# Fixes #123
# Relates to #456
#


# ====================
# Checklist:
# - [ ] Title is concise and follows Conventional Commits specification
# - [ ] No sensitive information included (tokens, passwords, keys, etc.)
# - [ ] Code has been self-tested and passed
# ====================
#
# Please remove all comment lines (lines starting with #) before committing
